In March 2016, Wärtsilä had launched the new Wärtsilä WTT-40 transverse thruster at the Seatrade Cruise Global convention being held in Fort Lauderdale, U.S. This first variant is part of Wärtsilä’s new transverse thruster series and features a 4000 kW power level and a 3.400 mm diameter controllable pitch propeller, neither of which has been open in Wärtsilä’s current product range. While Wärtsilä has designed and built large, up to 5500 kW, transverse thrusters as customized versions, the WTT-40 and others in the WTT range address customer demands for high power transverse thrusters for bow and stern applications. The company has enhanced its offering with this launch.

